# Naming Conventions

## General

- Use clear, readable names — avoid abbreviations and technical jargon
- Variables and functions: `camelCase` with descriptive intent
- Types and interfaces: `PascalCase`
- Config constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. `DEFAULT_AUDIT_SCOPE`, `QUICK_AUDIT_CRITERIA`)

## Files

| Folder | Pattern | Example |
|--------|---------|---------|
| config | `{name}.config.ts` | `audit.config.ts` |
| utils | `{name}.util.ts` | `wcagMapping.util.ts` |
| hooks | `{domain}.hooks.ts` | `audit.hooks.ts` |
| contexts | `{Name}Context.tsx` | `AuditContext.tsx` |
| components | `{ComponentName}.tsx` | `CriterionCard.tsx` |
| types | `{domain}.ts` | `finding.ts` |

## Audit data keys

| Key | Description |
|-----|-------------|
| `auditScope` | Selected scope tier: `quick`, `typical`, `full_aa`, or `full_aaa` |
| `auditType` | Type of audit: `web`, `design`, `document`, or `native_app` |
| `samplePages` | Array of pages included in the audit sample set |
| `auditResults` | Per-criterion per-sample-page evaluation outcomes |
| `findings` | Individual accessibility issues within an audit result |
| `scanResults` | Raw axe-core automated scan output per sample page |
| `criterionId` | WCAG criterion identifier (e.g. `"1.1.1"`) |
| `outcome` | Evaluation result: `passed`, `failed`, `inapplicable`, `cantTell`, `untested` |
| `priority` | Finding severity: `critical`, `major`, `minor`, `advisory` |
